# .gh-expected-identity — local-only per-developer pin for the gh-identity guard.
#
# Copy this file to .gh-expected-identity (which is gitignored) and add your
# GitHub login(s), one per line. The guard then blocks a mutating gh/git push
# whenever the active account is not in this list (strict-login mode).
#
# Omit the file entirely to use the accessibility fallback instead: the guard
# verifies the active account can reach the target repo, but cannot catch a
# wrong-but-also-authorized account in that mode.
#
# Find your login:        gh api user --jq .login
# Switch active account:  gh auth switch --user <login>
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored. Copying this file as-is
# (without uncommenting a login) yields zero valid logins, so the guard fails
# closed and tells you to fix it — replace the example below with your login.
#
# your-github-login
